<TITLE> Indian mobile firms add 6.3 mln GSM users in Aug </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, Sept 11 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - India's GSM mobile operators signed up 6.3 million users in August, an industry body said on Thursday. India, the world's second-largest market for wireless services, had 225.6 million GSM subscribers at the end of August, data from the Cellular Operators' Association of India showed The numbers do not include August additions by No 2 operator Reliance Communications. Reliance, which predominantly uses CDMA technology, had 52.5 million users at end-July. Market leader Bharti Airtel Ltd added 2.7 million users to take its subscriber base to 74.8 million. Vodafone Plc-controlled Vodafone Essar, the third largest operator, had 52.8 million users at end-August, 1.8 million more than a month ago, the data showed. State-run Bharat Sanchar Nigam Ltd added 573,862 users in August, taking its mobile customer base to 38.5 million
